application.model

Class Dinosaur

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.model.Dinosaur

  • public class Dinosaur
extends java.lang.Object
    The Dinosaur class is a representation of a dinosaur that is used by the Park class. Each dinosaur has a name, a type, and diet type. The dinosaur class contains an Override of the toString() method and has the following accessors and mutators: getZoneName, setZoneName, getZoneCode, setZoneCode, getThreatLevel, setThreatLevel.
    Author:
    Ivy Vasquez Sandoval (egi444) UTSA CS 3443 - Lab 8 Spring 2019
